The attempt to prevent Sakharov from running for a revamped Soviet Parliament has outraged Soviet intellectuals.
Sakharov and several other leading reformers, including the former director of the Soviet space institute, Roald Sagdeyev, failed to win nomination.
Sakharov Supported During secret balloting Friday at the prestigious Lebedev Institute, the physicists supported Sakharov's candidacy by a vote of 1,543 to 22.
